g the day she was the secretary to a high up official at Cybertronix.  Mr. - or John as he insistesd that she called him was nice enough, he seemed like he could be really cool, but their relationship had always been stricktly profesional.  Mai folded her short black skirt under her as she sat down in her chair and started to play back the messages that had been left over the night.  John was aprently not at work yet.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mai was in her mid 20's.  She had frizzed punk red hair (which to her delight her boss at Cybertronix had not made her change).  She only wore black, sleek clothing that together with her makeup and hair made her look like either an ex punk turned buisness woman or like a deranged cheerleader.  when she was not at work she was at home at her computer, polishing on her hacking abilities or reading about all the new technological advances.  Whenever she got the oportunity she would go to a club and dance the night away.<br>
<br>
But today was a monday.  And that meant another boring mind numbing day at Cybertronix, answering phones and making coffee.<br>
