<br>
&quot;The information on this will be downloaded into your central memory through the hook ups in your wrists. All basic information that humans use in everyday life will be yours. However, as far as emotions go, you will still need to learn about them. That is why I am here.&quot; <br>
<br>
Orlaith dismissed his other questions. Hesitantly, she walks to it and grabs its left wrist. The lightly tanned skin of her cheeks darkens to a soft rose hue. Its blank, unknowing stare sent chills down her spine. A slender finger presses down on a specific part of it's wrist, and down sinks the artificial flesh to reveal a bubble of metallic liquid surrounded by blinks and flashes and shots of light, electricity, and metal. With one hand, Orlaith held its wrist up, and with the other and her teeth, she tears open the plastic bag and gently places the chip into the liquid. Grinning, she presses the same spot again, and the liquid and it's surroundings are hidden once more. Orlaith steps back. Sighing, she smiles. She was in charge of what could be the thing to change history. Robots that are nearly human. Not knowing whether it was a good or bad thing, Orlaith smiles at the machine that would make her name known in the technological world.  <p><Br> <Br> <Br> <Br> Your head will collapse <Br> But there's nothing in it <Br> And you'll ask yourself <Br> Where is my mind? <Br> Where is my mind? <Br> Wheeeeeere iiis my mind?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uzulik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zulik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Angel of Death</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 2:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sci-Fi</span><hr size=1> .... okay..missiles.....hey..what the hell?<br>
