<br>
&quot;The rumbling in your stomach means that you need more power to run on. You were designed to be as human-like as possible. Humans need energy in the form of foods to live. You need energy in the form of that red gel to run. The gel can be taken in either through your 'mouth' or through a hook up just above your 'belly-button'. You are able to choose which way.&quot; <br>
<br>
She smiles again. Already her cheeks were beginning to hurt. ~'Remember to smile. He is new to life and living. He can feel and we do not want those feelings to be hurt. This is an assignment you cannot fool around with. Smile. Be cheery. And for gods sake be nice to the poor fellow. It'll be hard enough to deal with new feelings let alone deal with *your* attitude at the same time.'    Does Dr. Rosenworth always have to lecture me? I haven't messed up a single project or experiment ever. I've done everything right every single time. What does he think I'll do this time? I'm a scientist, not a child. Dried up old windbag needs to find something better to do with his time than lecture a perfectly good employee~<br>
<br>
